bib_record.title: Inclusive Scattering of Protons on Helium,Nickel and Tantalum at 500 MeV.

free_txt: The Triumf Cyclotron.
.A Direct Knockout Model and Quasi-Two-Body
Scaling Calculations.
.The Detector Telescopes
Consisted of Two Thin Delta-E Plastic Scintillators
Separated  by  a One Meter Flight Path to Provide
Time-Of-Flight  Information.   Following  these  was  a
Copper Degrader to Slow Down the Particles and a
7.6 Cm * 12.7 Cm  Diameter  Nai Detector to Provide
Energy Information.
The Scattered Protons were Detected in Range Telescopes
Symmetric with Respect to the Incoming Beam. Their
Solid Angles were Approximately 5 Millisr.
The Triumf Cyclotron.
The Beam Polarization
Was Continuously Monitored in a Beam Line Polarimeter.
